<h3>History</h3>
  <div id="change-72823" class="journal has-notes">
    <div id="note-1">
    <h4><a href="/issues/16809#note-1" class="journal-link">#1</a>
    <img alt="" class="gravatar" default="" rating="PG" src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d52f2b3c8e952dd826d8a04852870098?rating=PG&amp;size=24&amp;default=" ssl="false" title="" />
    Updated by <a href="/users/1573" class="user active">Stefan Schulte</a> <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2012-10-05" title="10/05/2012 02:55 pm">11 months</a> ago</h4>

    <div class="wiki" id="journal-72823-notes"><p>almost forgot: I see the error in the upstream 2.7.x branch</p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
  <div id="change-72832" class="journal has-notes">
    <div id="note-2">
    <h4><a href="/issues/16809#note-2" class="journal-link">#2</a>
    <img alt="" class="gravatar" default="" rating="PG" src="http://www.gravatar.com/avatar/d52f2b3c8e952dd826d8a04852870098?rating=PG&amp;size=24&amp;default=" ssl="false" title="" />
    Updated by <a href="/users/1573" class="user active">Stefan Schulte</a> <a href="/projects/puppet/activity?from=2012-10-05" title="10/05/2012 04:32 pm">11 months</a> ago</h4>

    <div class="wiki" id="journal-72832-notes"><p>looking more into it, it seems that the <code>to_line</code> hook (the one that merges the name, found environments, and the cronentry itself) is only implemented for the <code>crontab</code> record_type but not for the <code>freebsd_special</code> record type. To add more confusion it does work when the entry is initially created because puppet will assume a record_type of <code>crontab</code> in that case (<a href="/issues/3047" class="issue status-7 priority-4 priority-default closed" title="Cron entries using &quot;special&quot; parameter lose their title when changed (Duplicate)">#3047</a>).</p>

<p>Having two different <code>record_types</code> turns out to be a huge pain when one record should switch from a special record to a normal <code>crontab</code> record (<a href="/issues/3010" class="issue status-18 priority-4 priority-default closed" title="Crontab entries using &quot;special&quot; parameter can&#x27;t be converted to non-special entries (Merged - Pending Release)">#3010</a>) so I guess the best way is to have one record_type that can handle both entries.</p>
</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
